                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 10388.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Rockhill</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-12-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 13, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Bacon refers to department’s telegraphic instruction of June 8, 1906, and
                    instructs Mr. Rockhill to report whether the claims of American citizens have
                    been carefully substantiated, and to forward them to department for
                    approval.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
